  <description>Plants 1–2 m, branches spread-ing.  Leaves: petiole 5–10 mm; blade oblong, lanceolate, oblanceolate, or elliptic, 3–8 cm, margins entire or spinulose-serrulate, apex acute to abruptly short-acuminate, abaxial surface glabrous or sparsely hairy.  Inflorescences fascicled or solitary, sessile, dense, 8–30-flowered, 2–4(–5) cm; bracts ± deciduous, ovate, 2–2.5 mm.  Pedicels 2.2–2.5 mm.  Flowers: sepals whitish, broadly ovate, 1.5–2 mm, apex obtuse or rounded; corolla cylindric, 6–8 mm; filaments spreading-hairy, papillate; anthers 0.7–1.2 mm, with 2 awns, thecae divergent distally; ovary glabrous.  Capsules (4.5–)5–6 mm wide.  Seeds angular; testa firm, papillose.  2n = 22.</description>
